<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-21T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-21T17:00:00-05:00" n="101" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/918a: Circular telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)<note n="54" xml:id="d101fn54">Telegraphed
                            also on the same day to Peiping with instructions to repeat to Shanghai
                            and Nanking; and to London with instructions to repeat to Paris, Geneva,
                            Berlin, and Rome.</note></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-21T17:00:00-05:00">March 21, 1934—5
                            p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Texts of the exchange of informal letters between Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs Hirota and the Secretary of State were released to the press
                            today.</item>
                        <pb facs="0226" n="130" xml:id="pg_130"/>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>No negotiations of any sort have been in process or are being
                            conducted between the two Governments.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>You may so inform any inquirers.</item>
                    </list>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>